# TodoMVC Architecture Plan
## Leptos CSR + Axum + SQLite

### Project Structure
```
Cargo.toml              # Workspace root with leptos, axum, sqlx, tokio, serde
rust-toolchain.toml     # Nightly toolchain (required by Leptos)
tailwind.config.js      # Tailwind CSS config scanning .rs files
style/input.css         # Tailwind directives + TodoMVC base styles
migrations/
  001_create_todos.sql  # todos table: id, title, completed, display_order
src/
  main.rs               # Axum server: serves static files + API routes
  app.rs                # Leptos root App component, reactive state, filtering
  db.rs                 # SQLite pool init, embedded migrations
  models.rs             # Todo, CreateTodo, UpdateTodo (serde, sqlx derives)
  api.rs                # REST handlers: CRUD + toggle-all + clear-completed
  components/
    mod.rs              # Re-exports
    header.rs           # TodoHeader: title + input + toggle-all chevron
    todo_item.rs        # TodoItem: display, toggle, delete, inline edit
    footer.rs           # TodoFooter: count, filters (#/ hash routing), clear
tests/
  api_tests.rs          # Integration tests against in-memory SQLite
  e2e_tests.rs          # Full user-flow tests
.github/workflows/
  ci.yml                # clippy, fmt, test, build
README.md
```

### Issue Dependency Graph
```
Phase 1 - Foundation:
  #1 Cargo workspace + Leptos + Axum
    ├── #2 Tailwind CSS
    ├── #3 SQLite + migrations
    └── #4 CI pipeline

Phase 2 - Backend:
  #3 → #5 Todo model + shared types
  #5 → #6 CRUD endpoints
  #6 → #7 Bulk operations (toggle-all, clear-completed)
  #7 → #8 API integration tests

Phase 3 - Frontend:
  #6 → #9  TodoHeader component
  #9 → #10 TodoItem (toggle + delete)
  #10 → #11 Inline editing
  #10 → #12 TodoFooter (filters)
  #11 + #12 → #13 Toggle-all + wire up App

Phase 4 - Polish:
  #13 → #14 TodoMVC styling
  #14 → #15 Edge cases + empty states
  #15 → #16 E2E tests + README
```

### Key Design Decisions
1. **Leptos CSR mode** — client-side rendering, Axum serves static assets + JSON API
2. **Single crate** — no workspace splitting; frontend and backend in one crate with feature flags via cargo-leptos
3. **SQLite via sqlx** — compile-time checked queries, embedded migrations, in-memory DB for tests
4. **Hash-based routing** — `#/`, `#/active`, `#/completed` per TodoMVC spec (no server-side routing needed)
5. **Reactive signals** — Leptos signals for todo list, filter state; API calls update signals
6. **Tailwind CSS** — utility classes in .rs view macros, scanned by tailwind.config.js
7. **display_order column** — future-proofs ordering; default to insertion order
